# take-and-do

Next.js full-stack task/calendar/focus app. Scope: `TAD`.

## Structure

```
src/
  app/                    # Pages + app/api/**/route.ts
  components/
  hooks/
  server/
    controllers/          # BaseController subclasses
    services/api/         # DB/business logic per domain
    services/ai/
    services/google/
  db/
    schemas/
    dtos/                 # Zod DTOs for API boundary
  services/               # Client-side API services (*.client.service.ts)
  lib/                    # Framework plumbing ONLY (defineRoute, errors, styles)
  auth/
  stores/
  env/
```

## API route → controller → service

1. Zod DTOs in `db/dtos/`
2. Controller in `server/controllers/` extends `BaseController`, uses `initRoute({ bodyDto, responseDto, handler })`
3. API service in `server/services/api/<domain>.api.service.ts`
4. Route file wires exports:

```typescript
import { FocusController } from "@/server/controllers";
const controller = new FocusController();
export const GET = controller.getState;
```

5. Client calls via `services/<domain>.client.service.ts` → `fetch('/api/...')`

## Database

- Drizzle: `db/schemas/`, migrations in `drizzle/`
- Scripts: `db:generate`, `db:push`, `db:migrate`, `db:studio`

## UI

- Kanban: native HTML5 DnD, `@dnd-kit` where used
- Tailwind + some styled-components; no inline styles
- `@repo/ui` for shared primitives

## `lib/` boundary

Only thin third-party/framework wrappers. Domain logic → `server/`, `helpers/`, `services/`, `db/`.

## Auth

- `auth/guards.ts` — `requireNonAnonymous`, `getAccessByAuth` in controllers

## Testing

- Vitest, `src/**/*.test.ts`, node environment
- Controller tests in `server/controllers/tests/`

## Lint-staged

App-level husky runs eslint on staged `apps/take-and-do/**` files.
